A truly absurd and full of emotions year has just passed.  Looking ahead, the conditions are even better.  It was the year of the discovery of myself, of the love for me.  A year in which I brought into my life one extraordinary soul, let‚Äôs say two! üê∂  At the beginning of 2011, my post-Erasmus life began with a mediocre dramatic of what had happened in those 6 months in Spain.  A path that culminates in 2017 with the maximum acceptance of who I am and the desire to share it with everyone begins.  I never thought that in the last two years my life would have been so much disturbed by this new person of mine and I could not have wished better if not to end this decade with an embryon of what I already consider a family.  In 10 years maybe Instagram will no longer be there, I hope to remember how happy I was today in order to be even happier.  It has been a tough road, but the view from up here is priceless.  I hope that for you this year and this decade have been noteworthy as mine.  A happy new year and happy end of the decade to everyone.

Today my trip to Israel started and the first stop after a night in Tel Aviv was the old city of Jerusalem. 
A city that is described by many as divided into 4 but to me don‚Äôt exist. Yes, it's true, there are many distinct cultures, but that's the beauty of Jerusalem. Coexistence in a place so rich in spirituality make even the most atheistic of atheists a believer.
On the other hand, faith is not a question of which religion you believe but a set of beliefs. And sometimes these same beliefs in religions are similar if not equal. 
If it makes sense to come here for a person who does not believe? I say definitely yes. It can be experienced in a different way but no less credible and of less value for this reason.
It‚Äôs been just a day, can‚Äôt wait to explore more about this country!
